        labSteps: ['List code, configuration, secret, flag, and data items.', 'Assign source, owner, and environment.', 'Define validation and change authority.', 'Create rollback behavior for each type.'],
        evidence: ['Configuration inventory', 'Secret-boundary checklist', 'Feature-flag lifecycle plan'],
        answerGuide: ['Secrets are referenced, not copied.', 'Code, configuration, flags, and data have different recovery paths.', 'Flag rules include owner and removal criteria.', 'Configuration differences can be compared without exposing secret values.'],
        takeaways: ['The same code can behave differently because deployment state differs.', 'Secrets are configuration with stricter handling, not repository content.', 'Rollback planning must include flags, configuration, and data.'],
