        title: 'Blameless postmortems, root cause, and corrective action',
        objective: 'Create a learning-focused postmortem that distinguishes trigger, contributing conditions, root causes, impact, and preventive actions.',
        instruction: [
          'A postmortem documents what happened, impact, timeline, detection, response, contributing conditions, root causes, recovery, and follow-up actions. Blameless means the analysis avoids individual punishment and asks why actions made sense within the available system, incentives, information, and controls.',
          'A trigger is the event that exposed the weakness. Contributing factors increased likelihood or impact. Root-cause analysis should identify system conditions that can be changed. Saying human error rarely explains why review, automation, environment, or communication allowed the error to become impact.',
          'Corrective actions address the current defect. Preventive actions reduce recurrence or impact. Strong actions have owner, due date, priority, verification, and link to requirement, test, monitoring, runbook, or architecture. A postmortem without completed actions becomes documentation theater.',
        ],
        standard: 'Conduct learning-focused postmortems for significant incidents, produce evidence-supported causes, and track prioritized corrective and preventive actions through verified completion.',
        controls: ['Use a factual timestamped timeline.', 'Separate trigger from systemic causes.', 'Avoid person-as-root-cause conclusions.', 'Assign action owner, due date, and verification.'],
        failures: ['The postmortem blames the person who clicked deploy.', 'Actions say be more careful or improve monitoring without specifics.', 'The timeline omits delayed detection and communication.', 'Actions are created but never reviewed for completion.'],
